page.title: 11RIVERS AND CANALS
page.content:
The{Grand Union Canal}is now filling up with rainwater since it was drained in the early 1960's.The canal is teeming with{wildlife. No fish were visible, but there were a lot of{insects.}These included: Flies, pondskaters and diving beetles. By the{River Ouse,}there are water level posts and also next to the river there are beech trees and a lot of wildlife.There are bullrushes near the banks of the river and lillypads are floating on top.The river bed is mainly sand with reeds and weeds under the surface of the water.
